                <p id="moscow1">Yes, we do know it’s kind of cold in Moscow now, but you can do what the locals do in order to warm themselves up – drink loads of vodka. </p>
                <p id="show4">See more</p>
                <p id="moscow2" style="display:none">It’s not only vodka (or Putin) that makes Moscow special. If you’re looking for the real wintery, snowy atmosphere, where warm clothes, mittens and warm (or alcoholic drinks) will keep you going and you want to see some of the world’s
                    most amazing architecture, this is the place for you. From Red Square and St. Basil’s Cathedral to Lenin’s Mausoleum, Moscow really offers you numerous ways to experience the culture that goes far beyond the clichés seen in American
                    films. Bonus – Moscow is still preparing for Christmas, which is in the beginning of January per their calendar, so you get to relive Christmas time.

                </p>
                <p id="hide4" style="display: none">See less</p>
